1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:38,204
{\an8}I just imagined the person I like.

2
00:00:38,288 --> 00:00:39,914
{\an8}<i>Luisa Mae.</i>

3
00:00:51,468 --> 00:00:52,260
{\an8}Leave me alone.

4
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:01,561
{\an8}But if it's true that I am truly exposed,

5
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:04,147
{\an8}I prefer to face what awaits me here.

6
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:05,899
{\an8}<i>Even if I had to fight the Moravianos.</i>

7
00:01:05,982 --> 00:01:07,734
{\an8}I was born here in the Philippines,

8
00:01:07,817 --> 00:01:09,694
{\an8}and this is where I will die.

9
00:01:12,363 --> 00:01:15,241
{\an8}Alex, my life is here.

10
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:16,951
{\an8}Not abroad.

11
00:01:21,039 --> 00:01:21,956
{\an8}Mikoy?

12
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:24,459
{\an8}Huh?

13
00:01:39,182 --> 00:01:40,642
{\an8}Where are you going?

14
00:01:40,725 --> 00:01:43,520
{\an8}Nothing. That was Alex.

15
00:01:43,603 --> 00:01:46,022
{\an8}I think she just enjoyed
being with us too much,

16
00:01:46,105 --> 00:01:48,274
{\an8}so she wants to go out of the country.

17
00:01:49,317 --> 00:01:50,193
{\an8}Oh!

18
00:01:50,276 --> 00:01:52,028
{\an8}Well, that will be great!

19
00:01:52,529 --> 00:01:53,613
{\an8}What did you say?

20
00:01:53,696 --> 00:01:56,074
{\an8}Uh, that…

21
00:01:57,742 --> 00:01:59,035
{\an8}Let's think about it.

22
00:02:02,872 --> 00:02:04,332
{\an8}This is your fault!

23
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:06,626
{\an8}You got too close with them.

24
00:02:06,709 --> 00:02:07,544
{\an8}And now look,

25
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:09,838
{\an8}they want to see us every day.

26
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:16,719
{\an8}But I was hoping it would just be us.

27
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:18,513
{\an8}I don't want any competition.

28
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:24,853
{\an8}Sounds good!

29
00:02:26,020 --> 00:02:28,314
{\an8}Anyway, Mom is about to leave.

30
00:02:30,775 --> 00:02:31,609
{\an8}Oh, right!

31
00:02:31,693 --> 00:02:33,653
{\an8}Thank you, sweetheart! Thank you!

32
00:02:34,445 --> 00:02:35,613
{\an8}Mom!

33
00:02:46,332 --> 00:02:48,042
{\an8}Maybe we are overreacting.

34
00:02:51,754 --> 00:02:53,798
I'm not sure.
I can't answer that directly, Bok.

35
00:02:59,137 --> 00:03:00,555
How's the search for Vicek?

36
00:03:01,139 --> 00:03:03,725
It looks like Vicek got caught.

37
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:09,647
But if Mikoy is already compromised,
he will be dead soon, too.

38
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:21,242
Oh, Mom, are you sure you're okay?

39
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:23,870
- We won't walk you downstairs, okay?
- Oh, no, it's fine!

40
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:26,748
Because my chauffeur
is already downstairs.

41
00:03:26,831 --> 00:03:27,665
- He's waiting for me.
- Wow!

42
00:03:27,749 --> 00:03:30,585
He's just a driver!
Thanks a lot to Chiara!

43
00:03:30,668 --> 00:03:31,794
Of course, Mom!

44
00:03:31,878 --> 00:03:35,131
Don't forget. Eat properly,

45
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:37,717
and don't let the sweat dry on your back.

46
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:41,930
Chiara, I'm really sorry, but I just need
to visit our Tortahan Shop first.

47
00:03:42,013 --> 00:03:44,515
Mom! Mom, it's okay. No problem at all.

48
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:46,976
Oh, your medicines, your vitamins.
Take them!

49
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:49,604
And sleep early. You know, Manila

50
00:03:49,687 --> 00:03:51,522
is a city that never sleeps!

51
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:53,524
So you're not the city, dear, okay?

52
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:55,902
- Yes, Mom. Okay.
- All right, just pray.

53
00:03:55,985 --> 00:03:56,986
Mom, okay.

54
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:58,655
- Just pray.
- No problem, Mom!

55
00:03:58,738 --> 00:03:59,906
- Okay.
- Okay.

56
00:03:59,989 --> 00:04:02,283
- Okay. Good, good.
- Mom, you don't have to worry.

57
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:03,826
I'll take care of Mikoy.

58
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:04,953
I know that.

59
00:04:05,036 --> 00:04:07,163
I know you won't neglect my child.

60
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:09,332
Just go there once you're okay.

61
00:04:09,415 --> 00:04:10,959
Just tell me right away.

62
00:04:11,042 --> 00:04:12,377
And you, my dear!

63
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:14,712
Listen to Chiara.

64
00:04:14,796 --> 00:04:16,256
- Okay, Mom.
- Listen to Chiara!

65
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:18,758
- You might be the stubborn one!
- Of course, Mom!

66
00:04:18,841 --> 00:04:20,593
Of course, I'm scared of her!

67
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:21,803
She's the boss.

68
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:24,681
And you know, what else, my dear?

69
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:27,850
- What is it, Mom?
- If there's a problem, okay, don't--

70
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:29,936
Promise, I'll call you!

71
00:04:30,019 --> 00:04:32,563
- Yes, promise!
- And don't stay out too late!

72
00:04:32,647 --> 00:04:34,899
- Yes. You too, Mom. Let's go! Let's go!
- Right? Don't forget what I said.

73
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:36,359
- Okay, bye, Chiara!
- You didn't forget anything.

74
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:38,736
- Bye, Mom!
- Everything is complete.

75
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:49,455
Do you want me to cook for you?

76
00:04:56,629 --> 00:04:57,880
Shower?

77
00:04:59,590 --> 00:05:00,800
Come on. Let's shower?

78
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:03,636
Come on!

79
00:05:05,388 --> 00:05:06,639
Oh?

80
00:05:07,348 --> 00:05:08,558
Rock-paper-scissors?

81
00:05:11,102 --> 00:05:12,228
No.

82
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:15,106
What do you want?

83
00:05:18,776 --> 00:05:20,361
- Let's do tag. Tag!
- Huh?

84
00:05:21,779 --> 00:05:23,781
Oh, is that how it is?

85
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:30,621
Why would you even say that Mikoy
is like some disposable plastic?

86
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:37,253
That's the reality Mikoy got into
and the one we entered as well.

87
00:05:37,336 --> 00:05:38,755
Maybe you're forgetting that.

88
00:05:40,006 --> 00:05:42,633
Mikoy is a person. He is not a toy.

89
00:05:45,094 --> 00:05:46,429
You shouldn't be talking like that.

90
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:48,890
What do you mean,
I shouldn't talk like that?

91
00:05:48,973 --> 00:05:51,017
What's wrong with what I said?

92
00:05:52,643 --> 00:05:54,854
And we have enough
years of service to know

93
00:05:54,937 --> 00:05:57,273
that if our asset gets compromised,

94
00:05:57,356 --> 00:06:00,401
and also, we fail to give them
protective custody,

95
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:02,862
he or she will most likely be dead.

96
00:06:04,989 --> 00:06:05,823
To be honest,

97
00:06:05,907 --> 00:06:08,076
it seems like you're the one
getting compromised.

98
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:13,289
I've noticed lately the way you're
getting attached to Mikoy, our asset!

99
00:06:14,957 --> 00:06:17,460
Maybe you're forgetting
our asset is still a person.

100
00:06:17,543 --> 00:06:18,669
Mikoy is still human!

101
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:22,507
But the point is, he's our asset!

102
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:39,107
So that's how it is, huh?

103
00:06:45,446 --> 00:06:46,447
Come here!

104
00:06:48,324 --> 00:06:49,575
- Ouch!
- Ah!

105
00:06:53,830 --> 00:06:54,956
Are you okay?

106
00:06:55,039 --> 00:06:56,457
I'm fine, I'm fine.

107
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:58,876
I can still stretch. Look.

108
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:01,212
I still have full range of motion.

109
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:05,007
- Full range of motion, huh?
- Yeah.

110
00:07:14,016 --> 00:07:15,476
No more…

111
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:17,437
distractions.

112
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:20,106
Let's test how far

113
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:23,609
your range of motion goes.

114
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:26,446
Oh, that seems a bit much.

115
00:07:27,029 --> 00:07:29,282
- Oh, wow!
- I have full range of motion.

116
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:34,912
So this is the Bisdak Heartthrob
from Cebu?!

117
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:37,665
Ma'am?

118
00:07:37,748 --> 00:07:41,919
Call me Mama, since you took
a bullet for my daughter.

119
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:43,504
Right. Wait a minute.

120
00:07:43,588 --> 00:07:45,631
Why does this feel a bit awkward?

121
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,302
Ah, not really, ma'am.

122
00:07:49,385 --> 00:07:51,137
Oh, I mean, Mama.

123
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:52,805
We were just stretching.

124
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:55,475
- Oh! Just stretching?
- For therapy.

125
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:56,851
Did it stretch enough?!

126
00:07:56,934 --> 00:07:57,810
Mmm.

127
00:07:57,894 --> 00:08:00,271
The most stretchable of all.

128
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:16,162
Papa, if you're thinking
of sending him back to Vertex,

129
00:08:16,245 --> 00:08:17,788
not yet.

130
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:20,166
I know his wound has healed,

131
00:08:20,249 --> 00:08:23,669
but I'm worried
about the leftover traumas.

132
00:08:24,378 --> 00:08:25,796
Of course not, my dear.

133
00:08:37,058 --> 00:08:38,976
Ah! Kurt!

134
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:40,728
Bring out the food you brought!

135
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:45,441
It's time to stretch
our small and large intestines!

136
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:47,693
Let's eat!

137
00:08:57,161 --> 00:08:59,747
So, I'm doing this quick campus feature,

138
00:08:59,830 --> 00:09:02,833
you know, "Getting to Know
the Faces of the University".

139
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:04,252
It's super chill.

140
00:09:07,255 --> 00:09:08,464
That's cool.

141
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:09,632
Okay, sure.

142
00:09:20,142 --> 00:09:24,146
I tear up at social experiment videos
about kindness.

143
00:09:29,819 --> 00:09:32,321
If it comes, why not?

144
00:09:34,323 --> 00:09:36,367
I don't have an ideal guy.

145
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:39,537
You shouldn't really have standards
when it comes to relationships.

146
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:42,915
The most important thing is the profound
connection between the two of you.

147
00:09:42,999 --> 00:09:45,042
What's your idea of a perfect date?

148
00:09:47,753 --> 00:09:50,339
Sharing a bucket of sour cream popcorn.

149
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:51,799
I'm not complicated.

150
00:09:51,882 --> 00:09:54,552
Wait, where will you release this feature?

151
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:56,762
Um…

152
00:09:56,846 --> 00:10:00,808
Actually, I just really wanted
to get close to you,

153
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:03,102
so I could introduce you to my friend.

154
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:11,360
By the way, Papa.

155
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:15,114
I heard you had an emergency last night?

156
00:10:15,698 --> 00:10:16,532
Oh my!

157
00:10:16,616 --> 00:10:17,992
Someone from the Czech Republic arrived.

158
00:10:18,576 --> 00:10:19,702
Not a check, though.

159
00:10:19,785 --> 00:10:20,828
He's a no-go!

160
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:26,584
What do you mean by ruin the mood?

161
00:10:26,667 --> 00:10:28,836
You know I've never liked him, ever since.

162
00:10:29,337 --> 00:10:33,466
Shouldn't that make it better since
you've known each other for a long time?

163
00:10:33,966 --> 00:10:36,260
He even came to visit you
here in the Philippines.

164
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:44,310
Vicek?

165
00:10:52,443 --> 00:10:54,070
Oh, Vicek.

166
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:58,658
Will he be working for us again?

167
00:11:12,213 --> 00:11:13,464
Why is that?

168
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:15,800
Isn't he good security?

169
00:11:15,883 --> 00:11:17,593
Well, he looks like it.

170
00:11:17,676 --> 00:11:19,720
But did he steal money?

171
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:21,722
Oh! I know!

172
00:11:21,806 --> 00:11:23,015
He has many wives, right?

173
00:11:23,099 --> 00:11:25,101
I knew it!

174
00:11:30,689 --> 00:11:34,276
Let's just say that we had
a little disagreement.

175
00:12:09,603 --> 00:12:10,604
There he goes again.

176
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,940
Was that funny?

177
00:12:13,023 --> 00:12:15,067
That was funny to you, huh?! Oh!

178
00:12:15,151 --> 00:12:16,527
You scared Mikoy.

179
00:12:16,610 --> 00:12:18,654
He almost peed his pants.

180
00:12:38,507 --> 00:12:39,925
I'll just get something.

181
00:12:47,892 --> 00:12:48,976
Wait a minute.

182
00:12:49,059 --> 00:12:51,979
Why don't we have any dessert?

183
00:12:52,062 --> 00:12:53,731
Ah! Ah, yes! We do!

184
00:12:53,814 --> 00:12:55,524
Mom's crema!

185
00:12:55,608 --> 00:12:57,693
Oh! It's from my in-law. It's delicious!

186
00:12:57,776 --> 00:12:58,777
Could you get it, please?

187
00:12:58,861 --> 00:13:00,779
- Yes, I'll get it.
- Yes!

188
00:13:08,829 --> 00:13:12,166
Imagine, you go out of your way
to give him what he wants.

189
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:13,876
Exactly.

190
00:13:13,959 --> 00:13:17,087
But what he wants… is you.

191
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:19,465
But you know, I wouldn't do this

192
00:13:19,548 --> 00:13:21,967
if I didn't really owe him
a debt of gratitude.

193
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,762
Because this is so pathetic!

194
00:13:25,888 --> 00:13:27,515
That's too much!

195
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:28,474
But it's true.

196
00:13:29,558 --> 00:13:30,851
You know what?

197
00:13:31,352 --> 00:13:32,394
Just between us, okay?

198
00:13:32,478 --> 00:13:34,104
You two aren't even a good match.

199
00:13:34,188 --> 00:13:36,357
And you wouldn't even like him.

200
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,733
Why not?

201
00:13:37,816 --> 00:13:40,736
Because he's naive, a coward,

202
00:13:40,819 --> 00:13:42,571
and he doesn't fight back.

203
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:47,284
You know, the type who's too kind.

204
00:13:47,368 --> 00:13:49,787
So people take advantage of him,
and when they do,

205
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:51,705
he just lets it happen.

206
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:56,961
And another thing!
He doesn't know anything about life.

207
00:13:57,044 --> 00:13:59,922
He's already messed up,
and he'll just make things worse.

208
00:14:00,923 --> 00:14:02,258
What's wrong with you, Angelito?

209
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:03,551
It's getting worse!

210
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:06,929
So if I were you, stay away
from that friend of mine!

211
00:14:07,012 --> 00:14:08,514
You won't gain anything from him.

212
00:14:08,597 --> 00:14:10,808
You'll just waste your time on him.

213
00:14:12,434 --> 00:14:14,353
He sounds like a terrible guy.

214
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:16,438
- Exactly!
- Oh!

215
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:18,440
But who is this terrible guy?

216
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:21,151
Just so I'm sure I can avoid him.

217
00:14:21,986 --> 00:14:25,030
He's Angelito D. Pinagpala.

218
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:37,960
We're basically best friends now.

219
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:39,044
Really?

220
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:42,381
Yes! Didn't you say I should
build you up to her?

221
00:14:42,464 --> 00:14:43,507
So I became friends with her.

222
00:14:44,091 --> 00:14:45,551
She's so nice, right?

223
00:14:45,634 --> 00:14:48,345
I told you she's really easy
to be friends with!

224
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:49,346
Is that so?

225
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:52,641
You know, be careful with nice people.

226
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:55,936
Because they might be the ones
hiding dark secrets.

227
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:57,271
Oh? Who said that?

228
00:14:58,355 --> 00:15:02,151
No, I just watched a documentary
where the serial killer

229
00:15:02,234 --> 00:15:04,528
actually eats everyone he likes.

230
00:15:06,196 --> 00:15:07,740
What are you even watching?

231
00:15:07,823 --> 00:15:08,908
You should watch it too!

232
00:15:08,991 --> 00:15:11,994
It's very insightful about human behavior!

233
00:15:12,578 --> 00:15:14,830
There's no way Luisa Mae
is a serial killer.

234
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:16,206
How do you know?

235
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:17,333
Nothing.

236
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:18,876
I just know.

237
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,586
Like how

238
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:23,964
you knew Owen would get you into trouble
when he invited you to the bar?

239
00:15:24,048 --> 00:15:25,466
You talk too much!

240
00:15:25,549 --> 00:15:27,092
If you don't want to build me up,

241
00:15:27,176 --> 00:15:28,344
then don't!

242
00:15:28,969 --> 00:15:31,096
That's not what I meant!

243
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:32,848
All I'm saying is,

244
00:15:33,432 --> 00:15:36,477
don't focus on just one girl.

245
00:15:37,686 --> 00:15:38,771
Who?

246
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:40,105
You!?

247
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:51,992
Oh? Why are you getting mad?

248
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:53,786
It's true.

249
00:15:54,703 --> 00:15:56,330
We're not a thing.

250
00:15:56,413 --> 00:15:57,873
We're just friends, right?

251
00:16:02,544 --> 00:16:03,462
Whatever!

252
00:16:12,137 --> 00:16:14,848
I already briefed
the Senate Law and Order Committee

253
00:16:14,932 --> 00:16:19,937
and Intelligence Services
about our missing Czech, Vicek.

254
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:27,111
I wish they were as bald as me.

255
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:33,492
{\an8}NORBERTO S. RUIZ

256
00:16:33,575 --> 00:16:34,785
{\an8}Norberto…

257
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:37,538
{\an8}My friend.

258
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:50,467
What?! What, Senator?

259
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:12,531
Didn't I warn you that we shouldn't
tell him about anything!

260
00:17:12,614 --> 00:17:16,285
You even said it yourself
that Mikoy is smart!

261
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:44,021
That's what Vicek told me.

262
00:18:02,456 --> 00:18:05,334
See? You get triggered right away.

263
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:19,515
If that's what he said, it's not reliable.

264
00:18:48,377 --> 00:18:50,420
That's why we need to be more careful.

265
00:19:14,903 --> 00:19:16,405
{\an8}I've already done everything.

266
00:19:54,651 --> 00:19:56,612
Why are you dragging him into this?

267
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:23,180
Dad, Mikoy loves me.

268
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:26,308
And I love him very much.

269
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:28,936
So please,

270
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:30,520
don't drag him into this

271
00:20:30,604 --> 00:20:33,523
because he has nothing to do
with this mess.

272
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:36,193
And if he did, I would know.

273
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:40,280
I would notice if Mikoy
was doing something wrong.

274
00:20:49,164 --> 00:20:53,168
You think I can no longer do
what I used to do.

275
00:20:53,752 --> 00:20:55,629
Then you're wrong.

276
00:20:57,756 --> 00:20:58,840
Tonight,

277
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:02,636
I will finish the mission
that was given to me.

278
00:21:23,907 --> 00:21:26,451
CERTIFICATE OF APPRECIATION

279
00:21:39,798 --> 00:21:41,550
Are you just going to accept
their decision?

280
00:21:41,633 --> 00:21:44,052
Will you just let them decide for you?

281
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:51,435
If there was something he could do,
he would've done it already

282
00:21:51,518 --> 00:21:53,186
to protect me.

283
00:21:56,148 --> 00:22:00,610
Whatever is ordered from above…

284
00:22:03,447 --> 00:22:05,365
that's what we must follow.

285
00:22:13,415 --> 00:22:15,542
Especially not at this time.

286
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:20,547
Because of you, we are building cases
against the Moravianos.

287
00:22:22,841 --> 00:22:28,597
You will continue building cases
against the Moravianos.

288
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:31,475
Your mission will not stop,
even without me.

289
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:35,812
What if the one who replaces you
is not as supportive of this mission?

290
00:22:35,896 --> 00:22:38,690
What if they undermine
everything we're working on?

291
00:22:52,829 --> 00:22:55,082
I loved this agency.

292
00:23:17,145 --> 00:23:20,357
If I stay here,

293
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:23,443
this agency will probably
make more enemies,

294
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:26,154
and it will only make things
harder for you.

295
00:23:27,739 --> 00:23:34,079
Sometimes you just have to play along
with what those above you want.

296
00:23:39,209 --> 00:23:40,752
Even without me.

297
00:23:46,299 --> 00:23:51,096
I am confident in both of you.

298
00:23:52,514 --> 00:23:53,932
That you will finish this fight.

299
00:24:12,450 --> 00:24:13,535
Are you okay?

300
00:24:23,336 --> 00:24:24,671
Wow.

301
00:24:26,506 --> 00:24:28,049
That's impressive, huh?

302
00:24:28,717 --> 00:24:31,344
Since when did you learn
how to speak Czech?

303
00:24:32,179 --> 00:24:35,515
Nothing, just on the app.

304
00:24:36,683 --> 00:24:39,603
But seriously, are you okay?

305
00:24:44,024 --> 00:24:45,317
Do you want the truth?

306
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,694
No, I want the lie.

307
00:24:48,486 --> 00:24:49,529
Of course.

308
00:24:49,613 --> 00:24:51,156
Of course, I want the truth.

309
00:24:51,239 --> 00:24:52,949
You said it before, right?

310
00:24:53,533 --> 00:24:56,828
We're already part of each other's lives.

311
00:25:16,431 --> 00:25:19,726
He says I'm too distracted because of you.

312
00:25:22,604 --> 00:25:26,399
He doesn't understand
that I have to focus on you.

313
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,653
Especially in case someone
takes you away from me.

314
00:25:30,612 --> 00:25:31,613
What?

315
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:35,325
That seems impossible anyway.

316
00:25:35,408 --> 00:25:38,536
Because I'm already locked in your heart.

317
00:25:39,829 --> 00:25:42,832
Actually… I can't even find the key.

318
00:25:43,583 --> 00:25:44,793
I threw it away.

319
00:25:46,628 --> 00:25:48,713
That's so cheesy.

320
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:51,883
No, but seriously,

321
00:25:52,425 --> 00:25:54,177
your dad has a point.

322
00:25:55,679 --> 00:25:58,431
Maybe because, you know…

323
00:25:58,515 --> 00:26:00,558
your life is getting off track.

324
00:26:01,268 --> 00:26:04,020
The life you left in Prague, right?

325
00:26:05,272 --> 00:26:07,774
Well, my life is here now.

326
00:26:09,317 --> 00:26:11,278
His name is Mikoy.

327
00:26:13,446 --> 00:26:14,614
Isn't that even cheesier?

328
00:26:17,909 --> 00:26:19,619
But you're right.

329
00:26:20,203 --> 00:26:24,124
I just need to take care of something,
and I will be free.

330
00:26:27,294 --> 00:26:31,298
I just have some business to handle,
and everything will be fine.

331
00:26:35,593 --> 00:26:37,178
And once I do that,

332
00:26:38,388 --> 00:26:41,141
I'll be free to be with you.

333
00:27:34,235 --> 00:27:35,820
- Are you busy?
- Not really.

334
00:27:35,904 --> 00:27:37,197
Can we have dinner?

335
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:39,532
Are you okay? You're acting so weird.

336
00:27:39,616 --> 00:27:42,494
You suddenly invite me
to watch a movie and have dinner.

337
00:27:42,577 --> 00:27:43,870
Are you dying?

338
00:27:44,996 --> 00:27:47,123
<i>You just want a simple life, right?</i>

339
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:48,249
Wait a minute, Angelito.

340
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:50,377
<i>What are these questions?</i>
<i>Where is this coming from?</i>

341
00:27:50,460 --> 00:27:51,920
Do you know something I don't?

342
00:27:54,547 --> 00:27:58,093
<i>This Norberto guy,</i>
<i>if something bad happens to him…</i>

343
00:27:58,176 --> 00:28:00,261
I'm pretty sure there
would be a big investigation,

344
00:28:00,345 --> 00:28:02,972
and that would put us
in a very bad situation.

